;The Lighthouse Island and the Lighthouse, also known as Three Sirens Inn
NOUNDEF 1302 rowboat

INUMBER 1399 
NAME 1302
WEIGHT 1000
ARTICLE a
SUBSTANCE HARDMETAL
HIDDEN



NUMBER 1203
NAME A Rocky Coastline
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777
                      
ITEM 0 1399

*DESCRIPTION_START
Rocks and seashells crunch under your feet as you walk along this isolated 
stretch of coast. A rocky breakwater extends far out into the ocean, and the 
waves crash against it, sending spectacular plumes into the air. Almost at 
the horizon, a lighthouse is highlighted against the sky. A rowboat to take 
you across to the island is usually moored here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
                                                                      
VARIABLE DaBOAT         
VARIABLE BOATHERE
VARIABLE BOATMOVE


IFPREVERB GO 0          
     CLEARVERB
     AFFECT 1204
     EQUAL DaBOAT PLRSINROOM
     EQUAL BOATHERE BOATMOVE
     AFFECT 1203            
     IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0
        IFVAR DaBOAT < 2
           ECHO PLAYER You climb into the small wooden boat and take a seat.
           ECHO OTHERS %n clambers into the rowboat.
           DISBAND
           MOVE 1204 
           AFFECT 1204
           ECHO OTHERS %n climbs into the boat and takes a seat.
           POSITION SIT
        ENDIF
        IFVAR DaBOAT = 2 
           ECHO PLAYER You start to step into the boat, but realize there isn't enough room this trip.
           ECHO OTHERS %n looks appraisingly at the boat, and then steps back from it.
        ENDIF           
        IFVAR BOATHERE ! 0
           ECHO PLAYER The boat isn't here right now.
        ENDIF
     ENDIF
           

NOUNDEF 1304 oars

INUMBER 1397   ;oars
NAME 1304
TURNABLE
ARTICLE some
SUBSTANCE WOOD
VOLUME 1000
WEIGHT 1000
HIDDEN     

NOUNDEF 1305 jetty

INUMBER 1396
NAME 1305    ;jetty
ARTICLE a
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 10
HIDDEN

                
NUMBER 1204
NAME In the Rowboat
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777

ITEM 0 1397      
ITEM 1 767
ITEM 2 1396

*DESCRIPTION_START
The breeze hints at winter winds to come, a bit stiffer and cooler than the 
summer zephyrs. Two polished oak benches face each other and a set of wooden 
oars are already in place in the oarlocks. A burnished brass plaque embedded 
in the side of the boat is engraved with instructions. Looking out toward the 
island, you think you can make out an outcropping of rocks that may be a jetty.
*DESCRIPTION_END
            
RELOGIN 1203         

VARIABLE BOATMOVE

IFTOUCH 2
   IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 5
      CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER You can't reach that from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

     
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You see instructions engraved in black letters.
ENDIF            


IFPREVERB STAND  -1
   IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 5
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You start to stand, but the boat rocks dangerously, so you sit back down quickly.
      ECHO OTHERS %n starts to stand up, almost flipping the boat over.
    ENDIF
ENDIF

   
   
IFPREVERB READ 1 
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Engraved on the plaque in black letters you read:
   ECHO PLAYER   Provided compliments of Three Sirens Bed & Breakfast
   ECHO PLAYER       PUSH the oars to fit them into the oarlocks.
   ECHO PLAYER     PULL the oars to move the boat across the sound.
   ECHO PLAYER    When you reach the island, step out onto the jetty.
   ECHO PLAYER         The boat will make its way back home.
ENDIF

                   
VARIABLE ROWING

IFPREVERB PUSH 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0   
        IFVAR ROWING = 0
          ECHO PLAYER You fit the oars into the oarlocks and prepare to row the boat across the sound to the island.
          ECHO OTHERS %n fits the oars into the oarlocks and prepares to row across the sound.
          plrevent 4
          CONTPLREVENT  
          EQUAL FLAG1 1
          EQUAL ROWING 1
        ENDIF
        IFVAR ROWING ! 0
           ECHO PLAYER Someone else is already rowing the boat.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 0
         ECHO PLAYER The oars are already in the oarlocks and the boat is underway.  
      ENDIF
ENDIF
           

IFPREVERB LOOK 0
   CLEARVERB    
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0
     IFVAR ROWING = 0
       ECHO PLAYER The oars are lying in the bottom of the boat, waiting for you to push them into the oarlocks.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR ROWING ! 0
       ECHO PLAYER Someone else has already fitted the oars into the oarlocks.
     ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 0
      ECHO PLAYER You watch as the oars cut smoothly into the water, moving the boat across the sound.   
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ROWING = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You'll have to push the oars into the oarlocks first.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ROWING ! 0     
    IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You push off from the shore, pulling the oars through the water.
         ECHO OTHERS %n pulls on the oars, and the boat glides out onto the water.
         AFFECT 1203
         ECHO ALL You stand on the shore and watch as the rowboat pulls away from the shore.
         AFFECT 1204
         EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
         ADD BOATMOVE 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 0
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME ! 0
          ECHO PLAYER  You realize you can't pull the oars in midstroke.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR BOATMOVE = 1
       IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
          ECHO PLAYER You pull the oars through the water cleanly, pleased that it seems so easy.
          ECHO OTHERS The boat moves cleanly out onto the sound as %n pulls the oars.
          EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
          plrevent 4
          CONTPLREVENT
          ECHO ALL The boat turns slightly in the current, heading toward the small island ahead.
          ADD BOATMOVE 1
        ENDIF
     ENDIF
     IFVAR BOATMOVE = 2
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
           ECHO PLAYER You pull the oars through the water, your shoulders beginning to feel the effort.
           ECHO OTHERS %n pulls on the oars, moving the boat across the sound. 
           EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
           plrevent 4
           CONTPLREVENT
           ECHO ALL The current moves the boat more swiftly toward the island, and you realize that you can just let it take over.
           ADD BOATMOVE 1
           plrevent 4
           CONTPLREVENT
           ECHO ALL The island is clearly in view now. You can see the jetty jutting out into the ocean from the rocky beach and make out a rope lined path leading up to the lighthouse.
           plrevent 4
           CONTPLREVENT
           ECHO PLAYER As the boat approaches the jetty, you realize you'd better give the oars one last pull to turn it in towards the shore.
           ADD BOATMOVE 1
         ENDIF
     ENDIF
     IFVAR BOATMOVE = 3
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
           ECHO PLAYER You start to dip the oars into the water, then realize that there's no need. You can just let the current do the work for now.      
        ENDIF
     ENDIF
     IFVAR BOATMOVE = 4
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
           ECHO PLAYER You give the oars one last pull, turning the boat in for a clean landing against the jetty.
           ECHO OTHERS %n dips the oars in one last time, turning the boat in for a clean landing against the jetty.
           plrevent 4
           CONTPLREVENT
           ADD BOATMOVE 1
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR BOATMOVE = 5
        IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
           ECHO ALL The boat bumps gently against the jetty as %n plays with the oars.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 2
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 5
           ECHO PLAYER You'll have to wait till the boat gets closer to the jetty.     
        ENDIF
        IFVAR BOATMOVE = 5     
           IFVAR POSITION = 0
              ECHO PLAYER You scramble out of the boat and onto the rock jetty.
              ECHO OTHERS %n scrambles onto the rock jetty.
              DISBAND
              MOVE 1205
           ENDIF
           IFVAR POSITION ! 0
                ECHO PLAYER You'll have to stand up first.
            ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 2
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0
        ECHO PLAYER Peering out toward the island, you think you see what looks like a jetty where you can dock the rowboat.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 1
        ECHO PLAYER You're almost positive now that the outcropping of rocks you can see is actually a jetty.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 2
        ECHO PLAYER As you get closer to the island, you can see that the jetty is a natural outcropping of rock that has been pressed into service as a mooring for small boats.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 3
        ECHO PLAYER The boat moves swiftly in the current, almost racing toward the jetty.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 4
        ECHO PLAYER You realize you'd better give the oars one last pull or you'll drift right past the jetty.                
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 5
        SHOWROOM 1205
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1    
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR BOATMOVE = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You look over the sides of the rowboat.
      ECHO OTHERS %n looks back at the shore.
      SHOWROOM 1203
   ENDIF
   IFVAR BOATMOVE ! 0
      ECHO PLAYER Looking back, you see the coastling receding. Ahead, the lighthouse island invites you to explore it.                  
      ECHO OTHERS %n gazes around at the surroundings with a deep relaxed sigh.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
     EQUAL ROWING 0
     EQUAL BOATMOVE 0
     AFFECT 1203
     EQUAL BOATMOVE 0
     EQUAL ROWING 0
ENDIF   

NOUNDEF 1306 lighthouse

INUMBER 1395
NAME 1306
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 10
ARTICLE a    
HIDDEN


 
NUMBER 1205
NAME The Lighthouse Jetty
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777              
EXIT E 1206


ITEM 0 1395 

           
*DESCRIPTION_START
The breeze off the ocean is brisk, tugging at your clothing playfully. This 
rocky outcropping serves as a mooring place for the rowboat that The Three 
Sirens thoughtfully provides for traveling back and forth to the mainland. 
The inn itself, a remodeled lighthouse, stands out against the sky to the 
north. Any other direction you look you see only the ocean. A few seagulls 
wheel and dive in the sky above you, giving an occasional joyous caw.
*DESCRIPTION_END

RELOGIN 101  
  
IFENTRY
   ECHO PLAYER You watch as the boat drifts back toward the mainland. You're not sure how, but it seems to be heading straight for the rocky stretch of coast where you found it.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The charming lighthouse stands in the center of this tiny island off the 
coast. A paved walkway to the east leads up to a small wooden deck with a 
few comfortable rocking chairs lining it. A painted wooden sign proclaims 
that you have found "The Three Sirens Inn"
*DESCRIPTION_END


NOUNDEF 1311 chowder
ADJDEF 1311 seafood

INUMBER 1393
NAME 1311
FOOD
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
ARTICLE some
parameter1 5 


IFPREVERB LOOK -1
CLEARVERB
ECHO PLAYER Poking through the thick creamy broth, you find chunks of lobster and crabmeat, haddock and clams. There seem to be just enough potatoes to make this bowl of chowder a meal.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
CLEARVERB
ECHO PLAYER The heavenly aroma of of the chowder makes your mouth water. 
ENDIF                                                                    
   
VARIABLE CHOWDER         

IFPREVERB EAT -1
CLEARVERB       
   ECHO PLAYER Tasting the chowder is like a bite of heaven. The sweet lobster meat melts in your mouth, a perfect counterpoint to the salty broth.
   ECHO OTHERS %n takes a bite of the chowder, closing %h eyes to savor the taste.
   ADD CHOWDER 1
    IFVAR CHOWDER = 5
      REMOVEITEM -1
    ENDIF   
ENDIF
           
ADJDEF 1398 hand-painted

NUMBER 1206
NAME Three Sirens Inn, Front Deck
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777
EXIT W 1205  
;jetty
EXIT N 1208  
;dock
EXIT E 1207
;Eastpoint

ITEM 0  215 ADJ1=197 ADJ2=791
ITEM 1  913 ADJ1=1398 ADJ2=1101
ITEM 2  350 VAL2=1211 


*DESCRIPTION_START
  It's the front deck of an old New England inn. Just about what you'd expect 
-- railings, rocking chairs, a door leading into the lobby. 
*DESCRIPTION_END

NUMBER 1211
NAME Three Sirens Inn, Lobby
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777                 
EXIT E 1212    
;dining room
EXIT W 1213    
;kitchen
EXIT N 1222

ITEM 0  350 VAL2=1206 
;front deck
ITEM 1 962 ADJ1=1091 ADJ2=599 VAL2=1214 
;stairs to second floor landing
ITEM 2 939 
;sofa
ITEM 3 409
;fireplace
ITEM 4 328
;desk
ITEM 5 236
;clerk
PUT 4  111 ADJ1=448
;book
       
*DESCRIPTION_START
It's the lobby of an old New England Inn, ditto the deck. Comfortable sofa, a 
desk behind which you see a clerk, a fireplace with a crackling fire roaring 
in it, and a guest book with comments from former guests of the establishment. 
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
   ECHO PLAYER The desk clerk looks up from his work as you enter.
   ECHO OTHERS The desk clerk looks up from his work as %n enters.
ENDIF

IFVERB GAZE 5
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk looks down to make sure he hasn't got soup on his tie.
ENDIF
   
IFPREVERB WAVE 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You wave to the desk clerk.
   ECHO OTHERS %n waves to the desk clerk.
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER He waves back to you.
   ECHO OTHERS He waves back to %n.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KISS 5
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You blow a kiss to the desk clerk.
    ECHO OTHERS %n blows a kiss to the desk clerk.
      IFVAR GEN = 0
         ECHO PLAYER The man gives you an odd look.
         ECHO OTHERS The man gives %n an odd look.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR GEN = 1
        ECHO PLAYER The man grins and winks at you.
        ECHO OTHERS The man winks at %n.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER He's standing behind the desk, silly! That must hurt!
   ECHO OTHERS %n kicks the desk!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB WINK 5
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR GEN = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The desk clerk hands you a long-stemmed red rose from a vase on the desk.
      ECHO OTHERS The desk clerk pulls a longstemmed red rose out the vase and hands it to %n.
      NEWITEM -1 836 ADJ1=560 ADJ2=774
    ELSE
      ECHO ALL The desk clerk winks and says, "Your usual room, %n?
    ENDIF
ENDIF       


IFPREVERB THUMP 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Hey! That's not very nice!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The desk clerk will talk to you if you ask him questions in a way he understands. Use one or two word phrases,
   ECHO PLAYER and be sure you end with a question mark so he knows you're asking.
ENDIF
           
IFSAY rooms?
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk smiles at you and says, "Yep, we got four of them, all different colors."
ENDIF

IFSAY colors?
   ECHO ALL "Sure," the man tells you. "Mrs. Olson has them color coded. Rose, Blue, Gold and Green rooms."
ENDIF

IFSAY Blue_Room?
   AFFECT 1215
   EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
   AFFECT 1211            
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book. "Yep," he says, "Top of the stairs right there."
      ELSE  
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book and shakes his head. "Nope," he says. "That one's rented."
      ENDIF
ENDIF


IFSAY Gold_Room?
   AFFECT 1216
   EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
   AFFECT 1211            
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book. "Yep," he says, "Top of the stairs right there."
    ELSE
       ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book and shakes his head. "Nope," he says. "That one's rented."
      ENDIF
ENDIF


IFSAY Green_Room?
   AFFECT 1219
   EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
   AFFECT 1211            
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
      ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book. "Yep," he says, "All the way to the third floor."
         ECHO ALL The man smiles. "View up there makes the climb worth it though." 
    ELSE  
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book and shakes his head. "Nope," he says. "That one's rented."
      ENDIF
ENDIF


IFSAY Rose_Room?
   AFFECT 1218
   EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
   AFFECT 1211            
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book. "Yep," he says, "All the way to the third floor."
         ECHO ALL The man smiles. "View up there makes the climb worth it though."
     ELSE
         ECHO ALL The man checks the guest book and shakes his head. "Nope," he says. "That one's rented."
      ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 111
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The desk clerk slaps his hand down on the guest book as you reach for it.
      ECHO OTHERS %n reaches for the guest book, but the desk clerk slap his hand down on it.
      ECHO ALL He says, "Sorry, those records are confidential."
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY dinner?
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk points east and says, "Yep, we serve dinner there round the clock. Be sure to try the chowder!"      
ENDIF

IFSAY breakfast?
   ECHO ALL The man nods toward the kitchen. "Mrs. Olson likes to serve breakfast in the kitchen there. Says it's cozier."
ENDIF

IFSAY Mrs._Olson?
   ECHO ALL The man nods. "The lady that owns this place. They say she got this place for a song because of the ghost."
ENDIF

IFSAY song?
   ECHO ALL The man scratches his head and says, "Well, I ain't much of a singer, but if you got time while you're here, ask me for a story."
ENDIF

IFSAY story?   
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk smiles at you, and says, "Well, now, they do say I tell that story well...if you're sure..."
   ECHO ALL "I could tell it for you."
ENDIF

IFSAY sure?
   ECHO ALL The man chuckles softly at %n. "You don't sound real sure there. 
   ECHO ALL "Maybe if it didn't sound like a question..."
ENDIF           

VARIABLE STORY

IFSAY sure
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk smiles happily and steps out from behind the desk.
   ECHO ALL He says, "Well, now, anyone who wants to hear it, join up with %n and we'll go somewhere more quiet for this."
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL He shouts, "Hey, Willie, cover the desk for a few, willya?"
   plrevent 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL A waiter from the dining room slips behind the desk, saying, "Sure thing! Gonna tell the ghost story, huh?"
   plrevent 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO GROUP The desk clerk nods and leads you up the stairs, all the way to the Lighthouse Room.
   AFFECT 1220
   EQUAL STORY 1
   AFFECT 1211
   MOVEGROUP 1220
   AFFECT 1220
   SHOWROOM 1220
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk says, "Just say 'ready' when you're ready to listen."
   IFNOITEM 9
      NEWITEM 9 236
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1211
   ECHO ALL The desk clerk nods and leads the group up the stairs.       
ENDIF
     

IFSAY ghost?
    ECHO all The man looks around nervously. He drops his voice to a whisper.
    ECHO all "Saw her myself once, I think," he says. "Lady all in white."
ENDIF

IFSAY lady?
     ECHO all The man glances toward the stairs. He says, "Standing right there, she was."
     ECHO all He frowns slightly. "I got work to do here," he says. "You want a room?"
     PLREVENT 2
     CONTPLREVENT 
     ECHO PLAYER The man grudgingly adds, "Mrs. Olson might know more about it. Think she's in the kitchen."
ENDIF

IFSAY Three_Sirens_Inn?
     ECHO ALL "Ayup," he says. "Named for those three rocks off East Point. 
     ECHO ALL They're the reason this lighthouse is here. 
     ECHO ALL Ships used to hang up on them all the time. Treasure still shows up on Eastpoint sometimes. 
ENDIF

IFSAY treasure?
   ECHO ALL The man nods to you. 
   ECHO ALL "Never been much of anything," he says. "Mostly little things, forks, combs that kinda stuff."
ENDIF

IFSAY Eastpoint?
   ECHO ALL "That's what we call that little point out behind the lighthouse," the man tells you. 
   ECHO ALL He smirks.
   ECHO ALL "Seems a kind of fancy name for it, don't it?"
ENDIF

IFSAY lighthouse?
    ECHO ALL The clerk quirks one eyebrow. 
    ECHO ALL "Sure," he says. "This used to be the old lighthouse. Go all the way to the top...
    ECHO ALL "and you'll see the old light's still there."
ENDIF
 
IFSAY kitchen?                                          
   IFVAR DAY = 1
     ECHO ALL The clerk nods toward the west. 
     ECHO ALL "Right through there," he says. "Mrs. Olson is getting breakfast ready."
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DAY = 0
      ECHO ALL The clerk nods toward the west.
      ECHO ALL "Course," he says, "It's awful late for breakfast. You might try the dining room for some dinner."
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY dining_room?
      ECHO ALL "Mrs. Olson makes the best seafood chowder!" he says. "And don't forget to check the wine list."   
ENDIF


