*DESCRIPTION_START
Directly in front of you as you step off the landing is a large picture 
window looking out toward the ocean. On your right is an oak door leading to 
the Blue Room, and on your left is the teak door to the Gold Room. Polished 
wood stairs lead back down to the lobby, and black wrought iron stairs climb 
to the third level of the lighthouse.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
                       A small brass plaque on the door reads, 
                                 "::The Blue Room::"
                          "Come in stress, leave refreshed."     

A half-basket of dried herbs hangs below the plaque. Tiny white rosebuds are
 interspersed with lavender and yarrow. A handlettered sign invites you to take a sprig.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
                      A small brass plaque on the door reads,
                               "::The Gold Room::"
                    "Blessed be who enter, rested be who leave"
A halfbasket of dried flowers hangs below the plaque. Buttercup blossoms are 
mixed in with deep gold blossoms. A handlettered sign invites you to take a 
blossom.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
Insert ocean view here
*DESCRIPTION_END


IFPREVERB OPEN 2
   AFFECT ITEMVAL2
   EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
   AFFECT 1214
   IFVAR DUMMY1 > 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER It is locked.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
           
IFPREVERB OPEN 3
   IFITEM 3 CLOSED
      AFFECT ITEMVAL2
      EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
      AFFECT 1214            
       IFVAR DUMMY1 ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER It is locked.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 954
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 4
         CLEARVERB
         RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
           IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
              ECHO PLAYER You carefully select a yarrow sprig and work it free.
              ECHO OTHERS %n carefully removes a yarrow sprig from the basket.
              NEWITEM -1 954 ADJ1=875 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=1317
            ENDIF
            IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
              ECHO PLAYER You carefully select a sprig of lavender and work it free.
              ECHO OTHERS %n carefully removes a sprig of lavender from the basket.
              NEWITEM -1 954 ADJ1=266 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=540
            ENDIF
            IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
               ECHO PLAYER You pull a sprig of lavender free, and a yarrow sprig comes with it.
               ECHO OTHERS %n pulls a sprig of lavender from the basket, and it catches a yarrow sprig. 
               NEWITEM -1 954 ADJ1=875 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=1317
               NEWITEM -1 954 ADJ1=266 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=540
            ENDIF
        ENDIF    
     ENDIF         
  ENDIF   
  IFPREVERB GET -1
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 95
       IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 4
          CLEARVERB
          RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
             IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You carefully work a deep gold blossom out of the basket.
                ECHO OTHERS %n plucks a deep gold blossom from the basket on the door.
                NEWITEM -1 95 ADJ1=266 ADJ2=483
             ENDIF
             IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
                ECHO PLAYER You pull a bright yellow buttercup blossom from the basket.   
                ECHO OTHERS %n pulls a bright yellow buttercup blossom from the basket on the door.
                NEWITEM -1 95 ADJ1=106 ADJ2=1111 ADJ3=1318
             ENDIF
             IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
                ECHO PLAYER You pluck a deep gold blossom and a bright yellow buttercup from the basket.
                ECHO OTHERS %n takes a gold blossom and a buttercup from the basket on the door.
                NEWITEM -1 95 ADJ1=106 ADJ2=1111 ADJ3=1318
                NEWITEM -1 95 ADJ1=266 ADJ2=483
             ENDIF
          ENDIF
       ENDIF
    ENDIF
    
