NUMBER 1220
NAME The Lighthouse Room
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CHANNEL 777

ITEM 0 962 VAL2=1217               
ITEM 1 1123

*Description_START
This room is currently under construction. Dust sheets cover everything, but 
you can make out the shapes of a bed and a sofa. In the center of the room 
stands the old light that once kept ships from scraping bottom on this rocky 
coast. The view from here is spectacular. You can turn in a circle and see in 
every direction as far as the horizon.
*Description_END

VARIABLE STORY

IFSAY ready
   IFVAR STORY = 1
        ECHO ALL The desk clerk glances around the room. He says, "I think this might have been her favorite room."
        plrevent 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL The desk clerk smiles softly, and begins his tale. You get the feeling that he won't hear interruptions.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL "It all happened 'bout a hundred years ago," he begins...
        plrevent 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL ...the lighthouse keeper was a young man name of Tyler. Married up with a local girl...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL They say she was the prettiest girl in town. He brought her out here...
        plrevent 5
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL As the desk clerk continues, his voice seems to weave a spell around you...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL Your surroundings seem to fade away...
        move group 1221
      ENDIF
  ENDIF

IFENTRY
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 3
        IFVAR DUMMY1 < 7
            ECHO ALL You catch the scent of lavender as something brushes past you.
        ENDIF
     ENDIF
      IFVAR STORY = 2
         ECHO ALL The desk clerk's voice slowly brings you back to your surroundings.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL He looks at you with a slight smile.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL "Guess she wasn't much like other girls her age," he says. "Didn't seem to mind having no company."
         plrevent 5
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL The two of them lived here happily for years. Every few days, Tyler would get into the boat...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL and either go to the mainland, or out to sea to replenish supplies.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL Even then, Lenore wasn't lonely. She would go sit on the rock at Eastpoint...
         ECHO ALL looking out to sea.
         plrevent 5
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL He gestures toward a window. 
         ECHO ALL "That's Eastpoint right out that window.
      ENDIF
  ENDIF     


IFPREVERB LOOK 1
   CLEARVERB
   SHOWROOM 1207
      IFVAR STORY = 2
         ECHO PLAYER As you watch, Lenore wanders into sight. She stands looking out to sea for a moment...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT  
         ECHO PLAYER ...then breaks off a sprig of lavender and tosses it into the water.
         plrevent 4
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO PLAYER Suddenly, she lifts her head as if she hears something, and looks directly at the window where you stand.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT         
         ECHO PLAYER You listen intently, and hear Tyler's voice calling.
         plrevent 4
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO PLAYER Lenore's face breaks out into a happy smile, and she turns and runs toward the jetty...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT         
         ECHO PLAYER ...her hair coming loose and blowing behind her as she runs.
         plrevent 4
         CONTPLREVENT   
         ECHO PLAYER You see a glint of sun on something silver for a moment, then the next wave washes up...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT         
         ECHO PLAYER ...and it is gone.
         EQUAL STORY 3
         plrevent 5
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO PLAYER The desk clerk sighs, looking at his watch.
         ECHO PLAYER "There's not much more to the story...got time to hear it?" he asks.
     ENDIF    
 ENDIF      
 
IFSAY yes
   IFVAR STORY = 3
      ECHO ALL He nods and continues.
      ECHO ALL "Well, you know that happy people don't leave ghosts behind...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL One sunny morning, Tyler set out to do a little fishing. When it got close to sunset...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL ...Lenore walked out to Eastpoint to watch for his return.
       PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The man pauses, looking toward the window again.
      plrevent 5
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL He quietly says, "Tyler never came back."
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL "Not that night, nor the next day..not ever."
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL He walks over to the window and looks out.
      plrevent 4
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL "Lenore lived here the rest of her life. Every day she walked out to Eastpoint...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL "and dropped a flower into the water, promising that she'd wait for him forever."
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The clerk blushes a deep crimson.
      plrevent 4
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL "They say that she rewards anyone who does the same by showing them treasure...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL "not that I hold with that...but some days I do it..."
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL He chuckles softly at himself and says, "Just because it makes me feel good."
      plrevent 4
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The clerk looks around, looking embarrassed. 
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL "Well," he says, "guess I've kept Willie from his work long enough.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT      
      ECHO ALL "Feel free to explore a bit, see what you find." He smiles and walks down the stairs.
      REMOVEITEM 9
      EQUAL STORY 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF
      
 
                      
Number 1221 
NAME Lighthouse Jetty, 1896
REGION 0
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777              
RELOGIN 1220

;lighthouse
ITEM 0 1395
;man
ITEM 1 633
;woman
ITEM 2 1126

           
*DESCRIPTION_START
The breeze off the ocean is brisk, tugging at your clothing playfully. This 
rocky outcropping serves as a mooring place for the rowboat used for traveling 
back and forth to the mainland. The lighthouse, stands out against the sky to 
the east. Any other direction you look you see only the ocean. A few seagulls 
wheel and dive in the sky above you, giving an occasional joyous caw.
*DESCRIPTION_END
      
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You sense immediately that this is young Tyler, the lighthouse keeper. He 
glances often at his new wife, a soft smile lighting his face whenever he does.
He is wearing a heavy navy-blue wool coat, a black knit cap, some sturdy 
black cotton trousers and some heavy black leather boots.
You notice a simple gold band on his left hand.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You see Lenore, a darkhaired beauty of no more than eighteen. Her brown eyes 
sparkle whenever she glances at Tyler, which seems to be often. 
She is wearing a heavy blue velvet cape, some sturdy black leather shoes, and 
a sparkling silver comb that holds her luxurious hair in an intricate braid.
*DESCRIPTION_END

                                         
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The charming lighthouse stands in the center of this tiny island off the 
coast. A paved walkway to the east leads up to a small wooden deck with a 
few comfortable rocking chairs lining it.
*DESCRIPTION_END         

IFENTRY
   ECHO ALL The clerks voice fades away, and you find yourself standing on the jetty.
   plrevent 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL As you watch, a young man climbs onto the jetty from a small rowboat...
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT   
   ECHO ALL ...ties it securely to a mooring post, then turns and offers his hand to the woman in the boat.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT   
        ECHO ALL A lovely young woman steps out onto the jetty, and looks around wide-eyed.
        PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL She beams happily at the man, exclaiming, "Tyler! You've made it all so pretty!"
        plrevent 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL Tyler smiles softly at his wife, reaching out to touch her cheek with a calloused finger.
         PLREVENT 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL "I wanted it to be the perfect setting for you, Lenore," he says.
        plrevent 4
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL The two look at each other for a long moment, and then join hands and walk toward the lighthouse.
        AFFECT 1220
        EQUAL STORY 2
        AFFECT 1221
        move group 1220
ENDIF   
        
